ensure and monitor attendance of the GFPS members and GAD key personnel to GAD required trainings to capacitate and enhance their knowledge and build their competencies on GAD related laws and GAD-related tools, among others; and

consider updating the GAD Code and include provisions identified under PCW Memorandum Circular No. 2009-001 dated September 16, 2009 and facilitate the drafting of the IRR and ensure compliance of the same for its effective implementation.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant compute for the actual amount of liquidated damages that should be demanded from the contractor. Moreover, scrutinize the information indicated in the documents particularly the period or dates being prescribed;

OIC-MAgO submit the necessary supporting documents and ensure that future transactions be supported with complete documentation;

Concerned officials and employees provide satisfactory explanation for the noted observations relative the non-operation of the portion of the projects and non-implementation in accordance with approved Program of Works and enforce the performance of the repair of the subjected portion of the projects from the contractor; and

Municipal Engineer ensure that the quality of works and the implementation of the projects is in accordance with the approved design, plans, and specifications and ensure that the location of projects has no problems/issues relative the Land Ownership and/or Road Right-of-Way before the lot was used for the implementation of the project.

We reiterated our recommendations that the:

Municipal Development Council (MDC) with the assistance of the OIC-MPDO reassess the necessity of pursuing the unimplemented PPAs of prior years, otherwise reprogram the same to a more needed developmental project. The Council should also properly plan and prioritize all activities to be implemented during the year; and

MBO and MDC appropriate sufficient fund for the complete implementation of the identified projects.

We also recommended that the:

Municipal Engineer formulate policy guidelines that will aide in the effective and efficient coordination, monitoring, reporting and evaluation of the status of implementation of the PPAs for the optimal utilization of 20% DF;

MDC with the assistance of the MPDO and MEO evaluate the status and condition of the implemented projects to assess whether completed projects are being used in accordance to the purpose for which it was constructed likewise evaluate if the projects implemented needs more funding to be more usable and beneficial to constituents;

Municipal Mayor with the assistance of the Municipal Accountant make a formal demand against Maravilla Trading and Althaea Enterprises for the refund of the excess payment totaling ₱9,049.56 brought by the deduction of liquidated damages to project cost and the Municipal Treasurer make the necessary remittance to the BIR for the underpayment of taxes;

Municipal Accountant make necessary adjustments for the understatement of asset account and income accounts; and

MDC with the assistance of the MBO and MPDO, revert the savings accumulated for the implementation of various projects out of 20% DF and evaluate and compute further for the savings from recently completed projects and reprogram the same to more developmental projects to help achieve the desirable socio-economic development and environmental outcomes of the Municipality.

